I heard you have to activate BIOS shadowing, so that your PC can use a copy of the BIOS ROM instead, allowing you to remove the chip while the PC is running and replace it with the chip to be programmed. Sounds very tricky, though!<br /><br />And yeah, you'd have to use the exact same kind of chip that's already there, so you'll have to check what it is.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Tue May 15, 2007 7:16 am</p><hr />
